<DATE_TIME> 2000-02-24 00:06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kings 7, Flames 2  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    CALGARY, Alberta (AP) -- Rob Blake and Donald Audette each had a goal and
two assists as the Los Angles Kings scored five third-period goals in a 7-2
victory over Calgary on Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
	   Blake scored his 16th goal at 14:11 of the third period to cap a flurry that
saw the Kings score five times against Fred Brathwaite in a 7:38 span.
</P>
<P>
	   The last three goals came on power plays as the frustrated Flames took three
consecutive penalties, two by Andrei Nazarov.
</P>
<P>
	   Luc Robitaille scored his 32nd goal and added an assist for the Kings to
extend his point streak to 11 games (10 goals, nine assists).
</P>
<P>
	   Aki Berg, Zigmund Palffy, Jason Blake and Jere Karalahti also scored for the
Kings, who have won six of their last eight.
</P>
<P>
	   Jarome Iginla and Jeff Shantz scored for Calgary, which led 2-0 after the
first period. Iginla added an assist to extend his point streak to 11 games.
</P>
<P>
	   The Flames, outshot 48-26, are 2-10-1 in their last 13 games.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
