	   Frontier sprouted beyond its roots as a local phone monopoly in Rochester -
a metro region of nearly 1 million people - by buying more than a half-dozen
long-distance carriers in the 1990s and becoming one of the nation's top 10
long-distance providers.
</P>
</TEXT>
