<TEXT>
<P>
   BREMERTON, Wash. (AP) -- Republican presidential candidate John McCain ran
into a slight delay getting his campaign out of Washington state Wednesday night
when a wheel on his plane got stuck in some mud at the airport in Bremerton.
</P>
<P>
	   McCain's state campaign director, Kris Wilder, said McCain's Boeing 727 was
taxiing in preparation for takeoff when the front wheel left the tarmac. He said
nobody was hurt.
