Vancouver in the Canucks' first game since Marty McSorley struck Vancouver's
Donald Brashear with his stick. McSorley, the Boston Bruins' enforcer who
blindsided Brashear Monday night in Vancouver, was suspended earlier Wednesday
for the rest of the season. Anaheim's Teemu Selanne had a goal and two assists
in the seesaw game against the Canucks.
</P>
