<HEADLINE> Tokyo Stocks Rise  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    TOKYO (AP) -- The dollar edged higher against the Japanese yen Thursday on
optimism over strength in the American economy. Tokyo share prices also rose.
</P>
<P>
	   The dollar bought 111.00 yen, up 0.42 yen from its level of 110.58 yen late
Wednesday in Tokyo but slightly below its late New York level of 111.30 yen
overnight.
</P>
<P>
	   The benchmark 225-issue Nikkei Stock Average closed at 19,571.44 points, up
51.89 points, or 0.27 percent. On Wednesday, the average closed up 128.97
points, or 0.67 percent.
</P>
<P>
	   In currency dealings, the dollar largely followed through from its overnight
strength in New York. There, the greenback gained after U.S. Federal Reserve
Chairman Alan Greenspan's testimony Wednesday before a Senate panel.
</P>
<P>
	   Greenspan, delivering the second half of his semiannual report to Congress,
said he expects the U.S. economy to remain strong.
</P>
<P>
	   In other currencies, the euro was traded at 111.24 yen, up from 111.10 yen
late Wednesday in Tokyo.
</P>
<P>
	   On the stock market, prices moved higher following an overnight rally by
technology and Internet stocks in New York.
</P>
<P>
	   Morning gainers included major technology blue chips and information
technology-related issues as investors were encouraged by a steep rise in the
Nasdaq composite index overnight.
</P>
<P>
	   In New York on Wednesday, the technology-rich Nasdaq closed up 168.21 points
at 4,550.33, a new closing high that surpassed the previous record of 4,548.92
set last Thursday.
</P>
<P>
	   The Dow Jones industrial average closed down 79.11 points at 10,225.73.
</P>
<P>
	   The broader Tokyo Stock Price Index of all issues listed on the first
section gained 22.81 points, or 1.37 percent, to finish at 1,690.05. The TOPIX
closed up 22.65 points, or 1.38 percent, the day before.
</P>
<P>
	   The yield on the benchmark 10-year Japanese government bond rose to 1.8700
percent from Wednesday's finish of 1.8400 percent. Its price fell 0.25 point to
99.41.
</P>
</TEXT>
