<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Estelle Harris Helps Seniors on Web  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    PALM DESERT, Calif. (AP) -- Estelle Harris, best known as George Costanza's
mom on "Seinfeld," will soon be helping seniors with questions about the
Internet.
</P>
<P>
	   "The Internet is a way to stretch, to grow, to be a part of life," the
actress said Tuesday about her new venture, www.askestelle.com. The site, with
partner and software giant Oracle, launches March 1.
</P>
<P>
	   The Web site will feature an Internet talk show geared for seniors. Harris
will be the show's host.
</P>
<P>
	   "Don't ask me how it's done because I don't know," she said, referring to
the technical aspects of producing an online talk show. "I'm just the
personality kid who wants to do, to help and to learn."
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
