<DATE_TIME> 2000-02-24 03:08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Smashing Pumpkins Suing Manager  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    LOS ANGELES (AP) -- The Smashing Pumpkins are suing their former manager for
fraud and breach of contract for allegedly abandoning the rock band at the start
of its European tour.
</P>
<P>
	   The Superior Court lawsuit, filed Tuesday, contends Sharon Osbourne "reneged
without notice or any warning on an agreement to manage the band" and that she
allegedly misappropriated $150,000.
</P>
<P>
	   The lawsuit, which seeks unspecified damages, contends Osbourne "conjured
absurd expenses" in misappropriating the money.
</P>
<P>
	   There were no telephone listings for Osbourne or her West Hollywood-based
Sharon Osbourne Management Co., which was also named as a defendant.
</P>
<P>
	   The band is on a 37-city autographing tour to promote its latest album,
"Machina -- Machines of God."
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-02-24-00 0308 </TRAILER>
