<HEADLINE> Dow Rises 10; Nasdaq Climbs 34  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    NEW YORK (AP) -- The Dow Jones industrial average is up ten points in
today's early going. Advancing and declining issues are evenly split on the New
York Stock Exchange.
</P>
<P>
	   The Nasdaq Composite Index is ahead 34 points and the Standard &AMP; Poor's 500
Stock Index is up a fraction.
</P>
<P>
	   We'll see what the Nasdaq can do for an encore after the index posted its
biggest single-day point gain ever yesterday.
</P>
<P>
	   The Nasdaq began today's session from a record high, so any additional gains
today would take it deeper into record territory.
</P>
<P>
	   Meantime, analysts say the Dow appears to be going through a rather volatile
bottoming process, testing support levels as it suffers through waves of
selling.
</P>
<P>
	   There could be a measure of support today from the Treasury market, where
bond prices are higher following data that showed a decline in demand for
durable goods last month.
</P>
