<HEADLINE> Clinton Signs Foreign Cops Bill  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- President Clinton signed a directive Thursday for a $10
million U.S. program to train foreign police forces.
</P>
<P>
	   Clinton, in a statement, said ``in peacekeeping missions from the Balkans to
East Timor, establishing basic law and order has been among the most important
-- and formidable -- challenges.''
</P>
<P>
	   The State Department is setting up an office for the program. Secretary of
State Madeleine Albright said it would improve U.S. capacity to provide police
overseas in coordination with the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
