<HEADLINE> AP Financial News at 3:10 p.m. EST  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   Thursday, Feb. 24, 2000
</P>
<P>
	   Dow Down 255.96; Nasdaq Off 45.45
</P>
<P>
	   NEW YORK (AP) -- Blue chip stocks dropped sharply today, pushing
the Dow Jones industrial average below 10,000, while the
technology-dominated Nasdaq composite index dipped lower after
yesterday's record-shattering run. Just before 3 p.m. EST the Dow
was down 255.96 at 9,959.77 adding to yesterday's 79-point drop.
The last time the Dow traded below 10,000 was Oct. 18, and its last
close below 10,000 was April 6, 1999, when it stood at 9,963.49. It
reached a record 11,722.98 on Jan. 14. The Nasdaq was down 45.45 at
4,504.88 after rising a record 168.21 points Wednesday to 4,550.33,
a new closing high. The Nasdaq had been down about 50 points
earlier in the session due to profit-taking.
</P>
