<HEADLINE> Ford Relocating Luxury Brands to CA  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    DETROIT (AP) -- Ford Motor Co. will consolidate the North American
headquarters of its luxury brands in a new California office, the company said
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
	   The new offices of the Premier Automotive Group will house the Jaguar,
Volvo, Aston Martin, Lincoln and Mercury brands. About 200 workers will be
relocated from New Jersey, where Volvo, Jaguar and Aston Martin have their
headquarters now.
</P>
<P>
	   About 800 people will work in the new building in Irvine, Calif., which is
scheduled to be completed by 2001.
</P>
<P>
	   Lincoln and Mercury are already based in California -- a location that has
drawn more interest from automakers who want a different perspective on consumer
tastes than Detroit or the East Coast can provide.
</P>
<P>
	   General Motors Corp. reopened a design studio in California last month,
joining an estimated 20 other studios, including independent contractors and
shops operated by Ford, Volvo, DaimlerChrysler AG, Volkswagen, Mazda, Honda,
Toyota, Nissan and Mitsubishi.
</P>
<P>
	   Ford said Volvo and Jaguar would keep offices in New Jersey open. About 150
of Volvo's 500 New Jersey jobs will be transferred, while 50 to 75 of Jaguar's
140 jobs will go to California. Doolan said engineering and sales functions
would stay in New Jersey.
</P>
<P>
	   The Premier Automotive Group will keep its worldwide headquarters in London.
</P>
