<HEADLINE> AP Financial News at 5:10 p.m. EST  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   Thursday, Feb. 24, 2000
Dow Ends Off 133.41; Nasdaq Up
</P>
<P>
	   NEW YORK (AP)-- Blue-chip stocks fell sharply today on persistent
interest rate fears, sending the Dow Jones industrial average
briefly below 10,000. The technology-dominated Nasdaq composite
index, which fluctuated throughout the day reached a new closing
high for the second day in a row. At the close of regular trading
on Wall Street, the Dow was down 133.41 at 10,092.63. In earlier
trading, the index fell as low as 9,944.02 before bargain hunters
stepped in. The Nasdaq finished up 66.91 at 4,617.24. Dow stocks,
particularly retailers and banks, are heavily swayed by interest
rates because rising rates slow borrowing and consumer purchasing.
</P>
<P>
	   Financial Figures
</P>
<P>
	   NEW YORK (AP)-- Financial figures at the close:
Dow Industrials:        10,092.63  - 133.41
