<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Lopez's Dress Leaves Fans Marveling  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    LOS ANGELES (AP) -- It was the most eye-popping part of the Grammys and a
day later fans were still pondering the tale of the tape. Just how did singer
Jennifer Lopez hold it all together in her revealing Versace dress?
</P>
<P>
	   Lopez's people say such details are too intimate to share, but fashion
watchers say it's tape that keeps plunging necklines like her's from opening too
wide. A deep "V" opened to Lopez's navel, where a large broach held the blue and
green print fabric in place.
</P>
<P>
	   "My guess is that it was double-faced cellophane tape," said Tom Julian, a
trend analyst with Fallon McElligott in New York. "It could have been very small
and very subtle. It definitely has to be invisible."
</P>
<P>
	   Versace officials did not immediately answer requests for details on how
such sheer, long-sleeved dresses stay put.
</P>
<P>
	   But one fashion magazine editor who traveled from New York to watch
Wednesday's awards ceremony speculated that the tape may have been sewn in to
the "V" with velcro.
</P>
<P>
	   "I think she looked absolutely stunning," said Merle Ginsberg, entertainment
editor at W magazine. "She can wear it."
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
