<BODY>
<HEADLINE> First Data Announces Job Cuts  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    OMAHA, Neb. (AP) -- First Data Resources Inc. has eliminated 400 jobs in an
effort to reduce expenses and streamline operations.
</P>
<P>
	   The company said Thursday that 280 salaried employees and 45 hourly workers
lost their jobs.
</P>
<P>
	   "It impacted all areas and all levels," spokeswoman Nancy Etheredge said.
</P>
<P>
	   First Data, which provides credit cards and transaction processing to banks
and oil companies, eliminated the jobs of 105 other employees in January.
</P>
<P>
	   The cuts came after First Data executives decided the company had
duplicative jobs, mismatched priorities and too many managers, Etheredge said.
</P>
<P>
	   "This action basically right-sizes our company," she said. "Our business is
very competitive, and we need to look for more and better ways to be more
efficient so we can continue to grow and reduce operating costs."
</P>
<P>
	   First Data is organizing a job fair to help terminated employees find
positions at other companies, Etheredge said.
</P>
</TEXT>
